\fs24 \cf2 Kathak:\'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\partightenfactor0

\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf2 We start in the most Northern state of Uttar Pradesh, which is home to the style of Kathak. The word Kathak originates from the coupling of the Sanskrit words 
\f1\i Katha
\f0\i0  which means story, and 
\f1\i Kathakar
\f0\i0  which is a storyteller [2]. Therefore, Kathak originated through storytellers that would travel the regions of North India, sharing stories through dance [2]. Through time, Kathak dancers became popularly known as dancers of the King\'92s Court. They were often asked to perform for royals, their guests, and the entire kingdom. Because they were recognized for their art, and were in such close proximity to Kings and the royals, Kathak dancers were given utmost respect and known to be among the higher social class amongst the common people. Kathak dance is characterized by it\'92s beautiful repetitive spins and intricate footwork. Compared to the rest of the dance forms, Kathak is has less leg bends an is done mostly standing straight. Take a look at the video below to see a glimpse of Kathak dance!\'a0\
